&lt;p&gt;The trouble here, is that this img tag will be processed by the browser (the client). This client does not have access to the filesystem of the HTTP server.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, you have either to define the /tmp directory to be a valid location of your HTTP server, using the files in /tmp/ directory (but note that it would serve any other file contained in this directory, potentialy a security risk).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Or you store these generated images in a subdirectory that is already served by your HTTP server.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It may also be possible to define this /tmp location on the server to be served by a script that would analyse the URL containing the image filename. This script would then open the file in /tmp/ and serve it.&lt;/p&gt;
