&lt;div class="post-text" itemprop="text"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Amazon S3 supports 2 types of object URLs:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;path style: &lt;strong&gt;$host/$bucket/$key&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;virtual host style: &lt;strong&gt;$bucket.$host/$key&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You can find more information about them here: &lt;a href="http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonS3/latest/dev/UsingBucket.html#access-bucket-intro" rel="nofollow"&gt;http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonS3/latest/dev/UsingBucket.html#access-bucket-intro&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The URL you're getting from the client should work regardless of the format. The format used depends on:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;format of the endpoint client is using - IPs result in path style URLs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;bucket name - some bucket names are not valid DNS names and will result in path-style as well&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;

